items.title: Anti-extremism center opens in former house of Auschwitz commandant
items.author: Associated Press
items.content:
<article>A U.S.-based organization is transforming the house of Auschwitz commandant Rudolf Höss into a research center devoted to fighting extremism, and is introducing it to the public on the 80th anniversary of the liberation of Auschwitz on Monday. items.title: LIVE: Palestinians set to cross into northern Gaza in vehicles
items.author: Associated Press
items.content:
<article>Live from Salah al-Din Street, the main north-south road running the length of Gaza, as Palestinians wait to return to their homes in the northern half of the coastal enclave by cars. Israel allowed Palestinians to return on foot from Wadi Gaza earlier today. Read more here: https://bit.ly/4hdWJZw

items.title: LIVE: Thousands of Palestinians return to northern Gaza
items.author: Associated Press
items.content:
<article>Live from Wadi Gaza as Israel allows Palestinians to return to heavily destroyed northern Gaza for the first time since the early weeks of the 15-month war with Hamas, in accordance with a fragile ceasefire. Thousands of Palestinians are headed north after waiting for days to cross. Read more here: https://bit.ly/4gdwXmK

#gaza #palestinian #israel #live</article>

items.author: Associated Press
items.content:
<article>Israel has yet to allow Palestinians to return to their homes in northern Gaza on foot through the so-called Netzarim corridor bisecting the territory, which extends from the Wadi Gaza river valley to Gaza City. items.title: UN peacekeepers' vehicle burns near Goma as rebels in Congo close in on the city
items.author: Associated Press
items.content:
<article>M23 has made significant territorial gains in recent weeks, encircling the eastern city of Goma, which has around 2 million people and is a regional hub for security and humanitarian efforts. Three U.N. peacekeepers from South Africa have been killed in fighting M23 rebels in eastern Congo, a political party and a trade union said Saturday. Read more here: https://bit.ly/3WCl2I3
